{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "0fb27d12-e493-46a9-ba71-c156e6ee4f0c",
    "name": "Server Setup Template API",
    "description": "Complete collection for the Express 5 + TypeScript + MongoDB backend template.\n\n## Quick start\n\n1. Set the `baseUrl` variable if your server is not on `http://localhost:8001`.\n2. Run **Auth → Register**, grab the 6-digit OTP from the activation email (or the database in development).\n3. Run **Auth → Activate Account** — the test script stores `accessToken` and `refreshToken` automatically.\n4. Every protected request inherits the bearer token from the collection. When the access token expires (15 min), run **Auth → Refresh Token**.\n\nOTP codes expire after 3 minutes and are invalidated after 5 wrong attempts. Rate limits: login 10/h, OTP send 3/15min, OTP verify 5/15min.\n\nFull written reference: `docs/api/` in the repository.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "auth": {
    "type": "bearer",
    "bearer": [
      {
        "key": "token",
        "value": "{{accessToken}}",
        "type": "string"
      }
    ]
  },
  "variable": [
    {
      "key": "baseUrl",
      "value": "http://localhost:8001",
      "type": "string"
    },
